# Laravel Folio Usage Guide

## Page-Based Routing

This project uses Laravel Folio for automatic page-based routing. Files in `resources/views/pages/` are automatically mapped to URLs based on their file structure.

## URL Mapping Examples

```
File Structure → URL
resources/views/pages/index.blade.php → /
resources/views/pages/about.blade.php → /about
resources/views/pages/projects/index.blade.php → /projects
resources/views/pages/projects/[id].blade.php → /projects/123
```

## Page Conventions

### File Naming
- Use kebab-case for file names: `about-me.blade.php`
- Index pages: `index.blade.php` for directory roots
- Dynamic segments: `[id].blade.php`, `[slug].blade.php`

### Page Structure
Each page should include:
1. Proper HTML5 doctype and meta tags
2. Consistent header/navigation
3. Main content area
4. Footer

### Example Page Template
```blade
<x-layout>
    <x-slot name="title">Page Title</x-slot>
    
    <div class="min-h-screen">
        <!-- Hero Section -->
        <section class="py-20">
            <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
                <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold">Page Heading</h1>
            </div>
        </section>
    </div>
</x-layout>
```
